class Person
String name

Room 1 r -- * p Person
A Person called p has A Room called r. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one Room called r.
A Room called r has some Persons called p. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Person is created, its Room must be assigned. When a Person is deleted, its Room is not deleted and its list of Persons is decreased. When a Room is deleted, its Persons are not deleted. They are assigned to another Room.
